<subSubSection pageId="5" pageNumber="306" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="5.[151,1437,153,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,328,728,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Comments</emphasis>
. Described from Europe where it is widespread (
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, L. &amp; Collins, D. &amp; Hastings, A." box="[896,1116,729,755]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" refId="ref18631" refString="Mound, L. A, Collins, D. &amp; Hastings, A. (2018) Thysanoptera Britannica et Hibernica. A guide to British thrips. Lucidcentral. org, Identic Pty Ltd, Queensland, Australia. Available from: https: // keys. lucidcentral. org / keys / v 3 / british _ thrips / (accessed 28 August 2019)" type="url" year="2018">
Mound 
<emphasis box="[988,1040,729,755]" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">et al</emphasis>
. 2018
</bibRefCitation>
), this species is known also from eastern North America and 
<collectingCountry box="[532,684,765,791]" name="New Zealand" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">New Zealand</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, L. A. &amp; Walker, A. K." box="[701,974,765,792]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="1 - 140" refId="ref19005" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Walker, A. K. (1986) Tubulifera (Insecta: Thysanoptera). Fauna of New Zealand, 10, 1 - 140. https: // doi. org / 10.7931 / J 2 / FNZ. 10" type="journal article" year="1986">Mound &amp; Walker 1986</bibRefCitation>
). In 
<collectingCountry box="[1026,1132,765,791]" name="Australia" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Australia</collectingCountry>
, it has been reported from 
<collectingCountry box="[151,315,801,827]" name="Norfolk Island" pageId="5" pageNumber="306">Norfolk Island</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Mound, L. A. &amp; Wells, A." box="[330,576,800,827]" pageId="5" pageNumber="306" pagination="183 - 210" refId="ref19054" refString="Mound, L. A. &amp; Wells, A. (2015) Endemics and adventives: Thysanoptera (Insecta) Biodiversity of Norfolk, a tiny Pacific Island. Zootaxa, 3964 (2), 183 - 210. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / zootaxa. 3964.2.2" type="journal article" year="2015">Mound &amp; Wells 2015</bibRefCitation>
) and is here recorded from southeastern Queensland.
</paragraph>
